      {
        "block_label": "figure_title",
        "block_content": "Figure 1: High-level pipeline of our attack: Given the target sample  $ x_{0} $, we first add noise based on Equation 1 and feed it to the target model shaded in blue. At each sample step, we can compute a loss L using Equation 2 to derive the gradients. Gradients from all sample steps (with appropriate subsampling and aggregation operations) are used as features to train the attack model for MIA.",
